@startuml Document_Upload_Sequence
!theme plain
title Document Upload and Processing Sequence

actor User
participant Frontend
participant "FastAPI Backend" as API
participant "Document Service" as DocSvc
participant "Docling Service" as Docling
participant "Vector Service" as Vector
participant PostgreSQL
participant ChromaDB
participant "File Storage" as Storage

User -> Frontend: Upload document (PDF/DOC)
Frontend -> API: POST /api/v1/documents/upload
API -> DocSvc: upload_document(file, user_id)

DocSvc -> Storage: Save file to uploads/
Storage --> DocSvc: file_path

DocSvc -> PostgreSQL: Insert document record
PostgreSQL --> DocSvc: document_id

DocSvc -> Docling: process_document(file_path)
Docling -> Docling: Extract text and metadata
Docling -> Docling: Create semantic chunks
Docling --> DocSvc: ProcessedContent

DocSvc -> Vector: add_document_chunks(chunks, embeddings)
Vector -> Vector: Generate embeddings
Vector -> ChromaDB: Store vectors with metadata
ChromaDB --> Vector: Success

Vector --> DocSvc: Stored successfully
DocSvc -> PostgreSQL: Update document status = "processed"
DocSvc --> API: ProcessedDocument

API --> Frontend: {document_id, status: "processed"}
Frontend --> User: Upload complete notification

note right of Docling
  Handles multiple formats:
  PDF, DOC, DOCX, TXT, MD
end note

note right of Vector
  Uses sentence-transformers
  for embedding generation
end note

@enduml
